            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I will close that ticket as browser bug for the time being. A possible workaround should be this:\n\n```\nclass ExhaustingMiddleware(object):\n\n    def __init__(self, app):\n        self.app = app\n\n    def exhaust(self, environ):\n        request = environ.get('werkzeug.request')\n        if request is not None:\n            while 1:\n                item = request.stream.read(4096)\n                if not item:\n                    break\n\n    def __call__(self, environ, start_response):\n        app_iter = self.app(environ, start_response)\n        for item in app_iter:\n            yield item\n        self.exhaust(environ)\n        if hasattr(app_iter, 'close'):\n            app_iter.close()\n\n\napp.wsgi_app = ExhaustingMiddleware(app.wsgi_app)\n```\n\nIf anyone else encounters a browser or situation where that breaks, I will dive into that further.\n"
